<item>
            <title>[LU-7815] pinger thread evict the export between MDTs.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7815</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In DNE failover tests, we found MDT is being evicted by another MDT because of pinger timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Lustre: soaked-MDT0007: haven&apos;t heard from client soaked-MDT0004-mdtlov_UUID (at 192.168.1.110@o2ib10) in 230 seconds. I think it&apos;s dead, and I am evicting it. exp ffff88080c87d800, cur 1456388330 expire 1456388180 last 1456388100
Lustre: soaked-MDT0006: haven&apos;t heard from client soaked-MDT0004-mdtlov_UUID (at 192.168.1.110@o2ib10) in 232 seconds. I think it&apos;s dead, and I am evicting it. exp ffff88078f6f3c00, cur 1456388331 expire 1456388181 last 1456388099
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which actually should not happen. It looks like we should not add MDS-MDS export to obd_chain_timed list. I will cook a patch soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
